Key Match Events: Devin Booker scored 34 points and the Phoenix Suns never trailed in a 114-106 victory over the Utah Jazz.
Booker had 22 points in the first half on 7-of-8 shooting, including 4 of 5 from 3-point range.
Kevin Durant scored 25 points for the Suns.
Grayson Allen had 14 points, nine in the final period.
Lauri Markkanen led the Jazz with 24 points and Collin Sexton had 20.
Walker Kessler had 16 points and 13 rebounds for Utah.
Drew Eubanks had 11 rebounds for Utah.
Allen hit his only 3-pointer of the game early in the fourth quarter to make it a six-point Suns lead and they pulled away after that.
Mason Plumlee scored the first five Suns points (six for the game) and finished with 10 rebounds.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Suns have won three of four since coach Mike Budenholzer reorganized the Suns’ rotation with Bradley Beal coming off the bench.
The Suns beat the Jazz for the third time this season.
Jazz played without regulars Jordan Clarkson, Keyonte George and John Collins, but still got contributions from reserves Svi Mykhailiuk and Cody Williams with 13 points apiece.
Beal had his lowest output since moving into a reserve role, scoring 12 points in 31 minutes.
Jusuf Nurkic did not play for the second straight game after serving a three-game suspension.
